                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13442166/comment/17529091",
                    "id": "17529091",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=dawsonlp7609",
                        "name": "dawsonlp7609",
                        "key": "JIRAUSER288744",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Larry Dawson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "This works fine on debian:latest, but breaks on Ubuntu. It turns out that ubuntu is missing the timezone setup and adding the following line to the docker file fixes the problem:\r\n{code:java}\r\nrun DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive TZ=Etc/UTC apt-get -y install tzdata {code}\r\nFixed in the docker code, but I'm not sure given this whether this is a bug in pyarrow or not\u00a0 - the code I'm running is pretty simple and doesn't have a functional dependency on the local timezone, so I don't think it should fail if the timezone hasn't been set up, but I have to admit, it's pretty basic functionality.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=dawsonlp7609",
                        "name": "dawsonlp7609",
                        "key": "JIRAUSER288744",
